    public interface ISwTextProps

    ISwTextProps: Entity class of the tresosDB model.

    This meta-class expresses particular properties applicable to strings in variables or calibration parameters.

    • Method Detail

      • getSwFillCharacter

        long getSwFillCharacter()
        Query the value of the attribute SwFillCharacter.

        Filler character for text parameter to pad up to the maximum length swMaxTextSize. The value will be interpreted according to the encoding specified in the associated base type of the data object, e.g. 0x30 (hex) represents the ASCII character zero as filler character and 0 (dec) represents an end of string as filler character. The usage of the fill character depends on the arraySizeSemantics.

        Returns:
        The value or null

      • getArraySizeSemantics

        ArraySizeSemanticsEnum getArraySizeSemantics()
        Query the value of the attribute ArraySizeSemantics.

        This attribute controls the semantics of the arraysize for the array representing the string in an ImplementationDataType. It is there to support a safe conversion between ApplicationDatatype and ImplementationDatatype, even for variable length strings as required e.g. for Support of SAE J1939.

        Returns:
        The value or null
